scatter /ˈskætə/

(scattering,scattered,scatters) 

1. V-T If you scatter things over an area, you throw or drop them so that they spread all over the area. 撒 

例： She tore the rose apart and scattered the petals over the grave. 她掰开玫瑰花，把花瓣撒在坟墓上。 

例： They've been scattering toys everywhere. 他们总是把玩具分散得到处都是。 

2. V-T/V-I If a group of people scatter or if you scatter them, they suddenly separate and move in different directions. 使散开; 散开 

例： After dinner, everyone scattered. 吃完饭，每个人都散开了。 

3.  →  see also scattered , scattering

